  "title": "Drafter #76722",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Fire Protection Services</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Drafter</strong></li><li>Working Location: Sims Ave (7mins walk from Aljunied MRT)</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Monday to Friday, 8.30AM – 5.30PM)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic $1,500 - $2,800 + VB</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare and revise Fire Plan (FP) system layout drawings and Building Plan (BP) drawings.</li><li>Interpret architectural, structural, and mechanical plans to coordinate fire protection systems.</li><li>Ensure drawings are clear, accurate, and include all details needed for construction or manufacturing.</li><li>Use CAD software to create and edit drawings.</li><li>Ensure all drawings comply with local codes and standards (e.g., NFPA) and meet client requirements.</li><li>Collaborate with engineers, designers, and project managers to reflect the correct design intent.</li><li>Maintain drawing documentation and assist with submissions to relevant authorities.</li><li>Make revisions based on feedback from engineers, consultants, and Authorities Having Jurisdiction (AHJs).</li><li>Review and update drawings to meet project standards and requirements.</li><li>Stay updated on building codes, industry standards, and materials.</li><li>Provide technical support and help solve issues during construction or manufacturing.</li><li>Organize and manage all drawing files and project documents.</li><li>Communicate clearly with project managers, clients, and other stakeholders.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Experience as a drafter in the fire protection industry is an advantage.</li><li>Diploma or certification in Drafting, Engineering Technology, or a related field.</li><li>Proficiency in AutoCAD software.</li><li>Understanding of fire codes (e.g., NFPA and SCDF local fire safety regulations).</li><li>Attention to detail; able to work independently and as part of a team.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please  <strong>#76722 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Rachael Lee | EA Reg No.: R2093131</p>",
